The paper deals with the problem of indexing highly-repetitive collections of strings, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper proposes a new data structure that combines multiple measures of repetition, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses practical tradeoffs and experiments with real-world datasets, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under computational complexity (cs.CC), data mining (cs.DM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG).
